---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const FORM_URL = "https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeZrmsHarnxvNoe5bOWe7Ji8CNNBAy8SO5upeG3vQ4qSCwDhQ/viewform";
---
<BaseLayout title="Submit an interface | ITR Atlas">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Submit to the atlas</h1>
    <p>Know an interface we're missing, think an entry should carry another calculation, or spotted a
       number that's off? Propose it below. Submissions are reviewed and re-derived by hand from the
       primary source, so there's no open write access.</p>
    <p>Have the inputs ready: the source paper or DOI, the reported accuracy and timing, and the
       number of targets (or the relevant modality-specific inputs). The reported ITR is only a
       cross-check. Every figure is re-derived from those inputs.</p>
    {FORM_URL
      ? <p><a class="cta" href={FORM_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open the submission form →</a></p>
      : <p class="pending">The submission form is being set up. Check back soon.</p>}
    <p class="alt">On GitHub? You can also <a href="https://github.com/tangemicioglu/itr-atlas/issues/new/choose">open an issue</a>
       for a new interface, calculation request, or data correction, or send a
       <a href="https://github.com/tangemicioglu/itr-atlas/blob/main/.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md">pull request</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose { max-width: 70ch; }
  .prose h1 { font-size: 28px; margin: 24px 0 8px; }
  .cta { display: inline-block; margin-top: 12px; background: var(--accent); color: #fff;
    padding: 10px 16px; border-radius: 8px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 14px; }
  .pending { color: var(--muted); }
  .alt { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 16px; }
  .alt a { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
